If the plane has a hydraulic system and a max rate of control deflection, though, enter how long it takes to go from center to fully-deflected., unit: secs

description: The current modelview matrix to draw in standard 'OGL' coordinates - valid only during draw callbacks, unit: Matrix4x4

label: Viewport
author: MobiFlight community

label: Is Reverse Float Z
author: MobiFlight community
description: True if current rendering is reverse-float-Z with clip control set ot 0..1.  False for conventional GL rendering., unit: Boolean

label: Is Reverse Y
author: MobiFlight community
description: True if current rendering is reversed-Y (+Y = down) - false for conventional +Y=up rendering.  This indicates how the framebuffer is set up - the transform stack will be set up to correctly flip Y if used., unit: Boolean

label: Using Modern Driver
author: MobiFlight community
description: True if current rendering is being done by a modern Vulkan/Metal driver.  False if we have the GL driver., unit: Boolean

label: Current Gl Fbo
author: MobiFlight community
description: During drawing and FL callbacks, this is the correct GL_FRAMEBUFFER binding to restore if you need to render off-screen.  Will be 0 when no bridge FBO is provided, unit: GLenum

label: Hardware Msaa Samples

description: This is the MSAA sample count for rendered windows.  Note that '1' means MSAA is not being used, not that MSAA is being used with a single sample count. , unit: count

label: Ice Inlet Heat On
author: MobiFlight community
description: De-ice switch, 0 or 1.  De-ice - inlet heat. This switch turns on de-icing heat in the engine air inlet keep ice from choking your engine. Engine 1 only, unit: boolean

label: Ice Prop Heat On
author: MobiFlight community
description: De-ice switch, 0 or 1.  De-ice - prop heat. This switch turns on de-icing of the propeller(s) to keep ice from building up on your prop. Engine 1 only, unit: boolean

label: Ice Inlet Heat On Per Engine
author: MobiFlight community
description: De-ice switch, 0 or 1.  De-ice - inlet heat. This switch turns on de-icing heat in the engine air inlet keep ice from choking your engine.  Per engine, unit: boolean

label: Ice Prop Heat On Per Engine
author: MobiFlight community
description: De-ice switch, 0 or 1.  De-ice - prop heat. This switch turns on de-icing of the propeller(s) to keep ice from building up on your prop.  Per engine, unit: boolean

label: Ice Window Heat On
author: MobiFlight community
description: De-ice switch, 0 or 1.  De-ice - windshield heat. This switch turns on windshield de-icing to keep ice from blocking your vision., unit: boolean

label: Ice Pitot Heat On Pilot
author: MobiFlight community
description: De-ice switch, 0 or 1.  De-ice - pitot tube heat. This switch turns on de-icing heat in the pitot tube. If it freezes up your airspeed indicator and altimeter stop working. Airspeed and altitude related autopilot functions are also affected., unit: boolean

label: Ice Pitot Heat On Copilot
author: MobiFlight community
description: De-ice switch, 0 or 1.  Pitot tube heat, co-pilot. This switch turns on de-icing heat in the co-pilot side pitot tube. If it freezes up your airspeed indicator and altimeter stop working. Airspeed and altitude related autopilot functions are also affected., unit: boolean

label: Ice Aoa Heat On
author: MobiFlight community
description: De-ice switch, 0 or 1.  AOA sensor heat. This switch turns on de-icing heat for the AOA sensor. If it freezes up your AOA indicator stops working. AOA sensor failure will also affect the aircraft's artificial stability system if it has one.  Pilot., unit: boolean

label: Ice Aoa Heat On Copilot
author: MobiFlight community
description: De-ice switch, 0 or 1.  AOA sensor heat. This switch turns on de-icing heat for the AOA sensor. If it freezes up your AOA indicator stops working. AOA sensor failure will also affect the aircraft's artificial stability system if it has one.  Copilot., unit: boolean

label: Ice Static Heat On Pilot
author: MobiFlight community
description: De-ice switch, 0 or 1.  Static port heat. This switch turns on de-icing heat for the static sensor. If it freezes up your altimeter, vvi and airspeed indicator stop working. Pilot., unit: boolean

label: Ice Static Heat On Copilot
author: MobiFlight community
description: De-ice switch, 0 or 1.  Static port heat. This switch turns on de-icing heat for the static sensor. If it freezes up your altimeter, vvi and airspeed indicator stop working. Copilot., unit: boolean

label: Ice Surfce Heat On
author: MobiFlight community
description: De-ice switch, 0 or 1.  De-ice - electric heat. This switch engages electrically heated leading edges. (All wings), unit: boolean

label: Ice Surfce Heat Left On
author: MobiFlight community
description: De-ice switch, 0 or 1.  De-ice - electric heat. This switch engages electrically heated leading edges. (Left wing), unit: boolean

label: Ice Surfce Heat Right On
author: MobiFlight community
description: De-ice switch, 0 or 1.  De-ice - electric heat. This switch engages electrically heated leading edges. (Right wing), unit: boolean

label: Ice Surface Boot On
author: MobiFlight community
description: De-ice switch, 0 or 1.  De-ice - pneumatic. This switch inflates flexible bladders on the wing leading edges to pop off accumulated ice. (All wings), unit: boolean

label: Ice Surface Boot Left On
author: MobiFlight community
description: De-ice switch, 0 or 1.  De-ice - pneumatic. This switch inflates flexible bladders on the wing leading edges to pop off accumulated ice. (Left wing), unit: boolean

label: Ice Surface Boot Right On
author: MobiFlight community
description: De-ice switch, 0 or 1.  De-ice - pneumatic. This switch inflates flexible bladders on the wing leading edges to pop off accumulated ice. (Right wing), unit: boolean

label: Ice Surface Hot Bleed Air On
author: MobiFlight community
description: De-ice switch, 0 or 1.  De-ice - bleed air. This switch directs warm air from the engines into the wing leading edges to keep them free of ice. (All wings), unit: boolean

label: Ice Surface Hot Bleed Air Left On
author: MobiFlight community
description: De-ice switch, 0 or 1.  De-ice - bleed air. This switch directs warm air from the engines into the wing leading edges to keep them free of ice. (Left wing), unit: boolean

label: Ice Surface Hot Bleed Air Right On
author: MobiFlight community
description: De-ice switch, 0 or 1.  De-ice - bleed air. This switch directs warm air from the engines into the wing leading edges to keep them free of ice. (Right wing), unit: boolean

label: Ice Surface Tks On
author: MobiFlight community
description: De-ice switch, 0, 1, or 2.  De-ice - TKS fluid. This switch activates the pump for the weeping wing, dissipating TKS fluid on the leading edges to keep them free of ice. 0 = Off, 1 = Norm, 2 = High. (All wings), unit: enum

label: Ice Surface Tks Left On
author: MobiFlight community
description: De-ice switch, 0, 1, or 2.  De-ice - TKS fluid. This switch activates the pump for the weeping wing, dissipating TKS fluid on the leading edges to keep them free of ice. 0 = Off, 1 = Norm, 2 = High. (Left wing), unit: enum

label: Ice Surface Tks Right On
author: MobiFlight community
description: De-ice switch, 0, 1, or 2.  De-ice - TKS fluid. This switch activates the pump for the weeping wing, dissipating TKS fluid on the leading edges to keep them free of ice. 0 = Off, 1 = Norm, 2 = High. (Right wing), unit: enum

label: Cowling Thermal Anti Ice Per Engine
author: MobiFlight community
description: De-ice switch, 0 or 1.  De-ice - inlet heat. This switch turns on thermal anti ice of the engine cowling and inlet. This takes hot bleed air from the HP compressor.  Per engine, unit: boolean

label: Ice Prop Tks On Per Engine
author: MobiFlight community
description: De-ice switch, 0, 1, or 2.  De-ice - prop TKS. This switch turns on de-icing of the propeller(s) with TKS fluid to keep ice from building up on your prop. 0 = Off, 1 = Norm, 2 = High. Per engine, unit: enum

label: Ice Auto Ignite On
author: MobiFlight community
description: De-ice switch, 0 or 1.  De-ice - auto-ignition. This switch turns on a continuous ignition source in the engine to automatically relight it if there is a flameout., unit: boolean

label: Ice Detect On
author: MobiFlight community
description: De-ice switch, 0 or 1.  Ice-detection: Turn this switch on to enable ice-detection... if the system detects ice, it will light up the ICE annunciator., unit: boolean

label: Ice Tks Fluid Liter
author: MobiFlight community
description: TKS de-icing fluid reserve. See sim/aircraft/specialcontrols/acf_tks_cap_liter for the plane's total capacity., unit: liter

label: Actuators/Dump All On
author: MobiFlight community
description: Dump all pressurization, 0 or 1., unit: boolean

label: Actuators/Dump To Altitude On
author: MobiFlight community
description: Dump pressurization to the current altitude, 0 or 1., unit: feet

label: Actuators/Cabin Altitude Ft
author: MobiFlight community
description: Cabin altitude commanded, feet., unit: feet

label: Actuators/Cabin Vvi Fpm
author: MobiFlight community

label: Actuators/Max Allowable Altitude Ft
author: MobiFlight community

label: Actuators/Air Cond On
author: MobiFlight community

label: Actuators/Heater On
author: MobiFlight community
description: Electrical heater grid on, 0 = off, 1 = flight max (consumes rel_HVAC amps), 2 = ground max (consumes 2x rel_HVAC amps, turned off by weight-off-wheels) - not needed on airplanes that are using hot bleed air and have no heaters, unit: boolean

label: Actuators/Fan Setting

label: Indicators/Fan Speed
author: MobiFlight community

label: Actuators/Engine Bleed Sov

label: Actuators/Apu Bleed
author: MobiFlight community

label: Actuators/Gpu Bleed
author: MobiFlight community
description: GPU bleed air valve, close or open. A GPU is supposed to be always available., unit: boolean

label: Actuators/Isol Valve Left

label: Actuators/Isol Valve Right

label: Actuators/Pack Left
author: MobiFlight community
description: Left pressurization pack, off or on. The left pack is supplied from the left side of the plane or through the left isolation valve and only available for airplanes made for 11.35 or newer, unit: boolean

label: Actuators/Pack Center
author: MobiFlight community
description: Center pressurization pack, off or on. The center pack is supplied from center duct, which can be supplied from a center engine, APU, GPU, or, via the isolation valves, the left and/or right ducts. This pack is the only pack available for airplanes made for X-Plane 11.33 or older, unit: boolean

label: Actuators/Pack Right
author: MobiFlight community
description: Right pressurization pack, off or on. The right pack is supplied from the right side of the plane or through the right isolation valve and only available for airplanes made for 11.35 or newer, unit: boolean

label: Indicators/Bleed Available Left

description: Bleed air available in the left duct, which can come from left engines or through the left isolation valve. , unit: ratio

label: Indicators/Bleed Available Center
author: MobiFlight community
description: Bleed air available in the center duct, which can come from a center engine, APU, GPU, or, via the isolation valves, the left and/or right ducts., unit: ratio

label: Indicators/Bleed Available Right

label: Indicators/Engine Loss From Bleed Air Ratio

label: Indicators/O2 Bottle Rem Liter

label: Indicators/O2 Bottle Pressure Psi
author: MobiFlight community

label: Indicators/Pilot Felt Altitude Ft

If TCAS is overriden, returns how many targets are actually being written to with the override. These are not necessarily consecutive entries in the TCAS arrays. , unit: integer

label: Pitch Ratio

label: Roll Ratio

label: Heading Ratio
author: MobiFlight community
description: This is how much the flight controls are deflected in heading after any stability augmentation, where -1.0 is full left, and 1.0 is full right., unit: ratio

author: MobiFlight community
description: This is how much the speedbrakes surfaces are extended, in ratio, where 0.0 is fully retracted, and 1.0 is fully extended., unit: ratio

author: MobiFlight community
description: Actual sweep, in ratio. 0.0 is no sweep deployment, 1 is max sweep deployment., unit: ratio

label: Thrust Vector Ratio
author: MobiFlight community
description: Actual thrust vector, in ratio. 0.0 is no thrust vector deployment, 1 is max thrust vector deployment., unit: ratio

label: Dihedral Ratio

label: Incidence Ratio

label: Flap Handle Deploy Ratio
author: MobiFlight community
description: This is the ACTUAL FLAP deployment for overall flap system, in ratio, where 0.0 is flaps fully retracted, and 1.0 is flaps fully extended. You should probably use the deployment for flap set 1 or flap set 2 to deflect the surfaces though.  This takes into account that flaps deploy slowly, not instantaneously as the handle is dragged., unit: ratio

label: Slat1 Deploy Ratio
author: MobiFlight community
description: Slat deployment, where 0.0 is slats fully retracted, 1.0 is slats fully extended. This variable applies to lading-edge flaps as well., unit: ratio

label: Slat2 Deploy Ratio
author: MobiFlight community
description: Slat deployment, where 0.0 is slats fully retracted, 1.0 is slats fully extended. This variable applies to lading-edge flaps as well., unit: ratio

label: Flap1 Deploy Ratio
author: MobiFlight community
description: This is the ACTUAL FLAP deployment for flap-set #1, in ratio, where 0.0 is flaps fully retracted, and 1.0 is flaps fully extended., unit: ratio

label: Flap2 Deploy Ratio
author: MobiFlight community
description: This is the ACTUAL FLAP deployment for flap-set #2, in ratio, where 0.0 is flaps fully retracted, and 1.0 is flaps fully extended., unit: ratio

label: Stabilizer Deflection Degrees
author: MobiFlight community
description: This is the actual stabilizer deflection with trim for all-moving horizontal stabilizers. This is the deflection you can see visually on airliners. This is in degrees, positive for leading-edge nose up., unit: degrees

label: Aileron Trim
author: MobiFlight community
description: Aileron trim, in part of MAX FLIGHT CONTROL DEFLECTION. So, if the aileron trim is deflected enough to move the ailerons through 30% of their travel, then that is an aileron trim of 0.3., unit: ratio

label: Elevator Trim
author: MobiFlight community
description: Elevator trim, in part of MAX FLIGHT CONTROL DEFLECTION. So, if the elevator trim is deflected enough to move the elevators through 30% of their travel, then that is an elevator trim of 0.3., unit: ratio

label: Rudder Trim
author: MobiFlight community
description: Rudder trim, in part of MAX FLIGHT CONTROL DEFLECTION. So, if the rudder trim is deflected enough to move the rudders through 30% of their travel, then that is an rudder trim of 0.3., unit: ratio

label: Rotor Trim
author: MobiFlight community
description: Rotor trim, in part of MAX FLIGHT CONTROL DEFLECTION. So, if the rotor trim is deflected enough to move the rotor through 30% of its travel, then that is a rotor trim of 0.3., unit: ratio

label: Water Rudder Deploy Ratio

label: Engine Rotation Angle Deg

description: This is the angle of the engine as it turns over, running 0 to 360 over and over again in normal operation. Engine speed can be different than prop rotation speed in clutched designs. This is radians per second., unit: degrees

label: Prop Rotation Speed Rad Sec
author: MobiFlight community
description: Radians per second rotation speed of the prop., unit: radians/second

label: Prop No Disc Rotation Angle Deg
author: MobiFlight community
description: This is the angle of the prop or engine-fan as it rotates. You will see this value circulate 0 to 360 degrees over and over as the engine runs and the prop or fan turns. This dataref NEVER shows the speed of the prop disc if it happens to be showing. This always tracks the actual prop.  Override witih /prop_disc/override per engine!, unit: degrees

label: Prop Pitch Deg
author: MobiFlight community
description: This is the ACTUAL pitch of the prop in degrees from its flat-pitch setting., unit: degrees

label: Prop Cone Angle Rad
